{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place ginger and garlic in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place onions and 2 Tbsp oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>8 min\/120°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Meanwhile, heat remaining 2 Tbsp oil in a large frying pan over a high heat. Fry beef in batches for 2-3 minutes until browned all over. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Add madras curry powder and reserved chopped ginger and garlic then fry <nobr>1 min 30 sec\/100°C\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add reserved browned beef and juices, tomato purée, water and beef stock cube then, replace measuring cup with simmering basket, and simmer <nobr>60 min\/98°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. With simmering basket still in place, reduce <nobr>10 min\/105°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add lemon juice and stir in with spatula. Serve with pilau or cumin rice and poppadoms."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["10 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","2 garlic cloves","100 g onions, quartered","4 Tbsp vegetable oil","600 g braising steak, diced (2 cm)","2 Tbsp madras curry powder","50 g tomato purée","300 g water, or enough to cover meat","½ beef stock cube (for 0.5 l)","2 Tbsp lemon juice"]}],"id":"r111503","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-TFmD6C4KsnA\/XZQxbmEPh0I\/AAAAAAAAcvI\/cOH3ddFgRSEZCLHkhVJoWgAnwtQkDkwewCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_rwrzddgWQR9X2hcF.png","title":"Beef Madras","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"35.7 g","fat":"20.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"4.8 g","calories":"1451 kJ \/ 347 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frying pan, hob","hintsAndTricks":["This curry can be made hotter by adding 1 or 2 halved fresh chillies in step 1.","Madras curry is thought to have originated in Madras (now Chennai) in South India, when it was probably a variation of a rich vegetarian curry. Our madras uses beef, and while this wouldn't be done in India where the cow is a sacred animal, it is a very popular combination in curry houses here."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}